The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 30: Persons receiving gifts will have to pay tax on it provided the value of the gift, in cash or kind, exceeds Rs 50,000, the income tax department said ahead of Diwali. The tax will have to be paid by the recipient by including the amount in his taxable income, the Central Board of Direct Taxes said.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 30: State-owned oil firms have slashed jet fuel prices by 2.1 per cent for the second time this month in line with softening international rates. The aviation turbine fuel (ATF) will cost Rs 45,235.94 per kilolitre in Calcutta against Rs 46,101.86 per kl now, with effect from midnight tonight.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 30: The countrys fiscal deficit stood at over Rs 1.82 lakh crore for April-August 2009, touching 45.5 per cent of the annual budget estimate of over Rs 4 lakh crore. The government had projected a deficit of 6.8 per cent of GDP this fiscal.                                                                                                                           
